{
  "segments": [
    {
      "id": 0,
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 1.0,
      "text": "climb would do."
    },
    {
      "id": 1,
      "start": 1.0,
      "end": 3.84,
      "text": "Right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "start": 3.84,
      "end": 7.68,
      "text": "So there's a lot of, you know, a couple of benefits to this."
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "start": 7.68,
      "end": 8.84,
      "text": "Obviously, the speed, right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "start": 8.84,
      "end": 11.56,
      "text": "Because if my query is really simple,"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "start": 11.56,
      "end": 13.48,
      "text": "then this thing might be enough."
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "start": 13.48,
      "end": 14.32,
      "text": "Right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "start": 14.32,
      "end": 16.6,
      "text": "And this is basically what SQLite does."
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "start": 16.6,
      "end": 17.52,
      "text": "Right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "start": 17.52,
      "end": 19.72,
      "text": "They have their own VM that interprets these op codes."
    },
    {
      "id": 10,
      "start": 19.72,
      "end": 20.92,
      "text": "But if the query has been run longer,"
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "start": 20.92,
      "end": 22.6,
      "text": "then, you know, if I have to wait six milliseconds"
    },
    {
      "id": 12,
      "start": 22.6,
      "end": 25.44,
      "text": "to get a machine code for this, that's, again,"
    },
    {
      "id": 13,
      "start": 25.44,
      "end": 29.28,
      "text": "that's a true amount of time."
    },
    {
      "id": 14,
      "start": 29.28,
      "end": 32.84,
      "text": "The other benefit, though, is that you now"
    },
    {
      "id": 15,
      "start": 32.84,
      "end": 36.76,
      "text": "can actually debug failed programs more easily"
    },
    {
      "id": 16,
      "start": 36.76,
      "end": 38.2,
      "text": "because you have this thing at the top."
    },
    {
      "id": 17,
      "start": 38.2,
      "end": 40.92,
      "text": "You have this interpreter for your bytecodes."
    },
    {
      "id": 18,
      "start": 40.92,
      "end": 44.16,
      "text": "So if you're running the Kapal version and it crashes,"
    },
    {
      "id": 19,
      "start": 44.16,
      "end": 46.76,
      "text": "you can then reverse that and figure out, OK, what lines"
    },
    {
      "id": 20,
      "start": 46.76,
      "end": 49.32,
      "text": "of the code generated that there's op codes"
    },
    {
      "id": 21,
      "start": 49.32,
      "end": 52.0,
      "text": "or whatever the machine code that failed for me."
    },
    {
      "id": 22,
      "start": 52.0,
      "end": 54.84,
      "text": "And then I can step through it with a regular debugger"
    },
    {
      "id": 23,
      "start": 54.84,
      "end": 56.64,
      "text": "at the top and walk through and figure out, OK, here's"
    },
    {
      "id": 24,
      "start": 56.64,
      "end": 60.76,
      "text": "what line of code am I tripping up on."
    },
    {
      "id": 25,
      "start": 60.76,
      "end": 61.44,
      "text": "Yes?"
    },
    {
      "id": 26,
      "start": 61.44,
      "end": 64.12,
      "text": "If you're using the bytecode compiler,"
    },
    {
      "id": 27,
      "start": 64.12,
      "end": 65.56,
      "text": "that's pretty short."
    },
    {
      "id": 28,
      "start": 65.56,
      "end": 68.6,
      "text": "That's going to be better than not doing it at all."
    },
    {
      "id": 29,
      "start": 68.6,
      "end": 69.28,
      "text": "Correct, yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 30,
      "start": 69.28,
      "end": 70.08,
      "text": "Save it is."
    },
    {
      "id": 31,
      "start": 70.08,
      "end": 72.4,
      "text": "Am I saying that if your query short"
    },
    {
      "id": 32,
      "start": 72.4,
      "end": 74.2,
      "text": "is the bytecode compiler going to be better"
    },
    {
      "id": 33,
      "start": 74.2,
      "end": 76.08,
      "text": "than doing anything down here?"
    },
    {
      "id": 34,
      "start": 76.08,
      "end": 78.12,
      "text": "Or like not doing any of that things,"
    },
    {
      "id": 35,
      "start": 78.12,
      "end": 79.92,
      "text": "definitely just be like that."
    },
    {
      "id": 36,
      "start": 79.92,
      "end": 83.32,
      "text": "It's not even a plus."
    },
    {
      "id": 37,
      "start": 83.32,
      "end": 85.56,
      "text": "It's top codes."
    },
    {
      "id": 38,
      "start": 86.36,
      "end": 88.32,
      "text": "Like the GAMM op codes."
    },
    {
      "id": 39,
      "start": 88.32,
      "end": 88.84,
      "text": "Right."
    },
    {
      "id": 40,
      "start": 88.84,
      "end": 91.28,
      "text": "But we're doing the jit here."
    },
    {
      "id": 41,
      "start": 91.28,
      "end": 93.24,
      "text": "Yeah, like the jit."
    },
    {
      "id": 42,
      "start": 93.24,
      "end": 96.08,
      "text": "This is the jit step."
    },
    {
      "id": 43,
      "start": 96.08,
      "end": 97.44,
      "text": "Like, look at the query short."
    },
    {
      "id": 44,
      "start": 97.44,
      "end": 99.08,
      "text": "Don't generate it in code at all."
    },
    {
      "id": 45,
      "start": 99.08,
      "end": 101.32,
      "text": "What about the client saying?"
    },
    {
      "id": 46,
      "start": 101.32,
      "end": 103.44,
      "text": "What kind of code?"
    },
    {
      "id": 47,
      "start": 103.44,
      "end": 104.8,
      "text": "Machine code or C++ code?"
    },
    {
      "id": 48,
      "start": 104.8,
      "end": 106.12,
      "text": "What are you saying?"
    },
    {
      "id": 49,
      "start": 106.12,
      "end": 108.6,
      "text": "The telegraphs run master."
    },
    {
      "id": 50,
      "start": 108.6,
      "end": 109.96,
      "text": "They don't do any of that."
    },
    {
      "id": 51,
      "start": 109.96,
      "end": 112.64,
      "text": "What how does bytecode compare to just"
    },
    {
      "id": 52,
      "start": 112.64,
      "end": 115.12,
      "text": "like not doing any core generation?"
    },
    {
      "id": 53,
      "start": 115.12,
      "end": 115.96,
      "text": "Oh, it's a question."
    },
    {
      "id": 54,
      "start": 115.96,
      "end": 118.16,
      "text": "The question is, how does, like, if I did this,"
    },
    {
      "id": 55,
      "start": 118.16,
      "end": 120.64,
      "text": "and don't do any code generation,"
    },
    {
      "id": 56,
      "start": 120.64,
      "end": 123.32,
      "text": "sorry, is that if I just have like a bus tub"
    },
    {
      "id": 57,
      "start": 123.32,
      "end": 125.72,
      "text": "and interpret a cell system, I don't do that"
    },
    {
      "id": 58,
      "start": 125.72,
      "end": 127.08,
      "text": "versus having this step."
    },
    {
      "id": 59,
      "start": 127.08,
      "end": 128.96,
      "text": "Is this step always going to be better?"
    },
    {
      "id": 60,
      "start": 128.96,
      "end": 131.36,
      "text": "Well, I mean, for like maybe really, really, really simple"
    },
    {
      "id": 61,
      "start": 131.36,
      "end": 134.48,
      "text": "queries, it's like one, maybe."
    },
    {
      "id": 62,
      "start": 134.48,
      "end": 137.4,
      "text": "But like, when things are running, you know,"
    },
    {
      "id": 63,
      "start": 137.4,
      "end": 141.8,
      "text": "more complex things, then I want this, absolutely."
    },
    {
      "id": 64,
      "start": 141.8,
      "end": 144.88,
      "text": "But like, you think of like, I can handle the short things"
    },
    {
      "id": 65,
      "start": 144.88,
      "end": 147.76,
      "text": "without going to the expensive step."
    },
    {
      "id": 66,
      "start": 147.76,
      "end": 150.6,
      "text": "But then when the bigger queries, more complex things show up,"
    },
    {
      "id": 67,
      "start": 150.6,
      "end": 154.8,
      "text": "bus tub is going to choke, this thing is going to rip through it."
    },
    {
      "id": 68,
      "start": 154.8,
      "end": 156.48,
      "text": "So it can handle both."
    },
    {
      "id": 69,
      "start": 156.48,
      "end": 159.92,
      "text": "And you're saying you can switch from bytecode"
    },
    {
      "id": 70,
      "start": 159.92,
      "end": 162.2,
      "text": "to the x86 code on the fly?"
    },
    {
      "id": 71,
      "start": 162.2,
      "end": 164.12,
      "text": "This question is, can I switch it from the bytecode"
    },
    {
      "id": 72,
      "start": 164.12,
      "end": 165.08,
      "text": "to x86 code on the fly?"
    },
    {
      "id": 73,
      "start": 165.08,
      "end": 166.04,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 74,
      "start": 166.04,
      "end": 170.72,
      "text": "Think of like, I take a query plan, I break it up."
    },
    {
      "id": 75,
      "start": 170.72,
      "end": 173.32,
      "text": "It's a pipelines and a high of different instances"
    },
    {
      "id": 76,
      "start": 173.32,
      "end": 174.68,
      "text": "of those pipelines running."
    },
    {
      "id": 77,
      "start": 174.68,
      "end": 177.0,
      "text": "Like a task instance, or any two"
    },
    {
      "id": 78,
      "start": 177.0,
      "end": 179.04,
      "text": "ones going to process 1,000 tuples."
    },
    {
      "id": 79,
      "start": 179.04,
      "end": 181.64,
      "text": "So I'm running, you know, like, my thread's running"
    },
    {
      "id": 80,
      "start": 181.64,
      "end": 183.36,
      "text": "this bytecode version of it."
    },
    {
      "id": 81,
      "start": 183.36,
      "end": 184.88,
      "text": "I process 1,000 tuples."
    },
    {
      "id": 82,
      "start": 184.88,
      "end": 186.8,
      "text": "When I'm done, I go check to say, hey,"
    },
    {
      "id": 83,
      "start": 186.8,
      "end": 188.44,
      "text": "is the compile version ready for me?"
    },
    {
      "id": 84,
      "start": 188.44,
      "end": 190.48,
      "text": "If it is, then I just slide that in and process"
    },
    {
      "id": 85,
      "start": 190.48,
      "end": 192.0,
      "text": "the next 1,000 tuples."
    },
    {
      "id": 86,
      "start": 192.0,
      "end": 193.36,
      "text": "And the logic is actually the same."
    },
    {
      "id": 87,
      "start": 193.36,
      "end": 196.32,
      "text": "So it's not like there's going to be like any difference"
    },
    {
      "id": 88,
      "start": 196.32,
      "end": 198.36,
      "text": "in the data that's generated, the result generated"
    },
    {
      "id": 89,
      "start": 198.36,
      "end": 200.64,
      "text": "from the bytecode version versus the compile version."
    },
    {
      "id": 90,
      "start": 200.64,
      "end": 202.68,
      "text": "It's all the same."
    },
    {
      "id": 91,
      "start": 202.68,
      "end": 203.48,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 92,
      "start": 203.48,
      "end": 206.44,
      "text": "How come you're guessing about how complex the query would"
    },
    {
      "id": 93,
      "start": 206.44,
      "end": 209.36,
      "text": "be and then choose some of the branches instead of having"
    },
    {
      "id": 94,
      "start": 209.36,
      "end": 211.56,
      "text": "to get on the same panel?"
    },
    {
      "id": 95,
      "start": 211.56,
      "end": 211.84,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "id": 96,
      "start": 211.84,
      "end": 215.48,
      "text": "A question is, can we be, can the optimizer be smart enough"
    },
    {
      "id": 97,
      "start": 215.48,
      "end": 219.04,
      "text": "here and recognize, oh, well, this query is select 1."
    },
    {
      "id": 98,
      "start": 219.04,
      "end": 221.48,
      "text": "I know I don't need to read any data or anything"
    },
    {
      "id": 99,
      "start": 221.48,
      "end": 222.12,
      "text": "expensive."
    },
    {
      "id": 100,
      "start": 222.12,
      "end": 223.8,
      "text": "So just skip all this."
    },
    {
      "id": 101,
      "start": 223.8,
      "end": 225.6,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 102,
      "start": 225.6,
      "end": 227.72,
      "text": "But when you start doing joins, and we'll"
    },
    {
      "id": 103,
      "start": 227.72,
      "end": 232.04,
      "text": "see this in a few weeks, the optimizer is going to be way off."
    },
    {
      "id": 104,
      "start": 232.04,
      "end": 238.16,
      "text": "So a simple threshold might be like, do this."
    },
    {
      "id": 105,
      "start": 238.16,
      "end": 239.6,
      "text": "Oh, we always have to do this."
    },
    {
      "id": 106,
      "start": 239.6,
      "end": 241.04,
      "text": "And then maybe it just always just in the background."
    },
    {
      "id": 107,
      "start": 241.04,
      "end": 244.16,
      "text": "And then maybe some triggers says, OK, after 20 milliseconds,"
    },
    {
      "id": 108,
      "start": 244.16,
      "end": 244.8,
      "text": "that's enough."
    },
    {
      "id": 109,
      "start": 244.8,
      "end": 247.2,
      "text": "Let me run this too."
    },
    {
      "id": 110,
      "start": 247.2,
      "end": 247.72,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 111,
      "start": 247.72,
      "end": 249.64,
      "text": "So can I say that on the average case,"
    },
    {
      "id": 112,
      "start": 249.64,
      "end": 251.24,
      "text": "it's like building on his point."
    },
    {
      "id": 113,
      "start": 251.24,
      "end": 253.28,
      "text": "And I say on the average case, it might be worse."
    },
    {
      "id": 114,
      "start": 253.28,
      "end": 255.44,
      "text": "But on the worst case, it would be really good."
    },
    {
      "id": 115,
      "start": 255.44,
      "end": 257.4,
      "text": "His statement is, can I say that on the average case,"
    },
    {
      "id": 116,
      "start": 257.4,
      "end": 261.32,
      "text": "it might be worse, but on the worst cases,"
    },
    {
      "id": 117,
      "start": 261.32,
      "end": 263.48,
      "text": "it would be, yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 118,
      "start": 263.48,
      "end": 268.6,
      "text": "But where that cutoff between, in that best case,"
    },
    {
      "id": 119,
      "start": 268.6,
      "end": 273.44,
      "text": "is the interpreted system would be better than compilation?"
    },
    {
      "id": 120,
      "start": 273.44,
      "end": 275.2,
      "text": "It depends on the hardware, depending on what you're doing."
    },
    {
      "id": 121,
      "start": 279.52,
      "end": 280.52,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 122,
      "start": 280.52,
      "end": 285.52,
      "text": "How many, for what sort of a state company would"
    },
    {
      "id": 123,
      "start": 285.52,
      "end": 288.2,
      "text": "please, like, the difference in milliseconds actually"
    },
    {
      "id": 124,
      "start": 288.2,
      "end": 289.76,
      "text": "matter?"
    },
    {
      "id": 125,
      "start": 289.76,
      "end": 291.76,
      "text": "His question is, for what kind of companies would"
    },
    {
      "id": 126,
      "start": 291.76,
      "end": 292.84,
      "text": "milliseconds matter?"
    },
    {
      "id": 127,
      "start": 292.84,
      "end": 294.84,
      "text": "Well, for one query."
    },
    {
      "id": 128,
      "start": 294.84,
      "end": 295.36,
      "text": "For one query."
    },
    {
      "id": 129,
      "start": 295.36,
      "end": 296.36,
      "text": "For one query, yeah."
    },
    {
      "id": 130,
      "start": 296.36,
      "end": 299.2,
      "text": "The same difference is 20 milliseconds."
    },
    {
      "id": 131,
      "start": 299.2,
      "end": 299.4,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "id": 132,
      "start": 299.4,
      "end": 302.2,
      "text": "So his question is, why do people care?"
    },
    {
      "id": 133,
      "start": 302.2,
      "end": 308.2,
      "text": "So on the extreme case are the high-frequency trading"
    },
    {
      "id": 134,
      "start": 308.2,
      "end": 309.72,
      "text": "guys."
    },
    {
      "id": 135,
      "start": 309.72,
      "end": 311.96,
      "text": "They're snort and cocaine, they're running"
    },
    {
      "id": 136,
      "start": 311.96,
      "end": 313.32,
      "text": "around fiber on the river."
    },
    {
      "id": 137,
      "start": 313.32,
      "end": 315.64,
      "text": "Like those guys, they want to measure queries"
    },
    {
      "id": 138,
      "start": 315.64,
      "end": 316.64,
      "text": "in microseconds."
    },
    {
      "id": 139,
      "start": 316.64,
      "end": 317.64,
      "text": "But is this an old lab?"
    },
    {
      "id": 140,
      "start": 317.64,
      "end": 319.68,
      "text": "Like this for specifically old lab workroom for both old lab"
    },
    {
      "id": 141,
      "start": 319.68,
      "end": 320.52,
      "text": "and old lab?"
    },
    {
      "id": 142,
      "start": 320.52,
      "end": 322.08,
      "text": "You could use this for both."
    },
    {
      "id": 143,
      "start": 322.08,
      "end": 324.76,
      "text": "So the high-frequency trading guys care a lot."
    },
    {
      "id": 144,
      "start": 324.76,
      "end": 329.8,
      "text": "For us mortals, the conventional wisdom"
    },
    {
      "id": 145,
      "start": 329.8,
      "end": 332.72,
      "text": "is 50 milliseconds."
    },
    {
      "id": 146,
      "start": 332.72,
      "end": 334.6,
      "text": "And that's usually for a transaction."
    },
    {
      "id": 147,
      "start": 334.6,
      "end": 338.08,
      "text": "And that number comes from internet advertising auctions."
    },
    {
      "id": 148,
      "start": 338.08,
      "end": 339.76,
      "text": "So when you go visit a web page and you're not"
    },
    {
      "id": 149,
      "start": 339.76,
      "end": 344.4,
      "text": "using ad blocker, the hosting company sends,"
    },
    {
      "id": 150,
      "start": 345.04,
      "end": 346.68,
      "text": "whoever's running the ad, say it's Google,"
    },
    {
      "id": 151,
      "start": 346.68,
      "end": 350.76,
      "text": "they send a request out to the different advertising"
    },
    {
      "id": 152,
      "start": 350.76,
      "end": 353.44,
      "text": "brokers, the auction houses, to say, here's this user"
    },
    {
      "id": 153,
      "start": 353.44,
      "end": 354.36,
      "text": "visiting this web page."
    },
    {
      "id": 154,
      "start": 354.36,
      "end": 356.08,
      "text": "And here's everything they know about you."
    },
    {
      "id": 155,
      "start": 356.08,
      "end": 357.84,
      "text": "They bundle that out into the request."
    },
    {
      "id": 156,
      "start": 357.84,
      "end": 359.0,
      "text": "And I think you then, the contract"
    },
    {
      "id": 157,
      "start": 359.0,
      "end": 361.16,
      "text": "is you have to respond in 50 milliseconds."
    },
    {
      "id": 158,
      "start": 361.16,
      "end": 363.4,
      "text": "What your bid is for the return of the ad."
    },
    {
      "id": 159,
      "start": 363.4,
      "end": 365.16,
      "text": "It might have gone down to like 40, 30 milliseconds."
    },
    {
      "id": 160,
      "start": 365.16,
      "end": 366.36,
      "text": "But that's roughly what it is."
    },
    {
      "id": 161,
      "start": 366.36,
      "end": 369.68,
      "text": "So the response time you have to get back is 50 milliseconds."
    },
    {
      "id": 162,
      "start": 369.68,
      "end": 371.92,
      "text": "So now, assuming we're around trip times,"
    },
    {
      "id": 163,
      "start": 371.92,
      "end": 373.72,
      "text": "so maybe it's some number less than that."
    },
    {
      "id": 164,
      "start": 373.72,
      "end": 375.52,
      "text": "So you got to run a query to go look up"
    },
    {
      "id": 165,
      "start": 375.52,
      "end": 378.2,
      "text": "and see whether I want to sell an ad to this person"
    },
    {
      "id": 166,
      "start": 378.2,
      "end": 381.4,
      "text": "within that time."
    },
    {
      "id": 167,
      "start": 381.4,
      "end": 382.32,
      "text": "There's another number, too."
    },
    {
      "id": 168,
      "start": 382.32,
      "end": 383.12,
      "text": "I think it's from Amazon."
    },
    {
      "id": 169,
      "start": 383.12,
      "end": 385.36,
      "text": "It says for every 100 milliseconds"
    },
    {
      "id": 170,
      "start": 385.36,
      "end": 387.6,
      "text": "that the Amazon product page is slower."
    },
    {
      "id": 171,
      "start": 387.6,
      "end": 390.08,
      "text": "They lose $1,000,000."
    },
    {
      "id": 172,
      "start": 390.08,
      "end": 393.0,
      "text": "I mean, I don't know if that's apocryphal."
    },
    {
      "id": 173,
      "start": 393.0,
      "end": 395.84,
      "text": "But there's some correlation between slower pages"
    },
    {
      "id": 174,
      "start": 395.84,
      "end": 398.24,
      "text": "equals less sales."
    },
    {
      "id": 175,
      "start": 398.24,
      "end": 399.08,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 176,
      "start": 399.08,
      "end": 403.04,
      "text": "I think that's the greatest small particle fix system."
    },
    {
      "id": 177,
      "start": 403.04,
      "end": 406.12,
      "text": "So if it's had more latency, then other people"
    },
    {
      "id": 178,
      "start": 406.12,
      "end": 407.28,
      "text": "get the same sales."
    },
    {
      "id": 179,
      "start": 407.28,
      "end": 409.28,
      "text": "Everyone has to optimize that."
    },
    {
      "id": 180,
      "start": 409.28,
      "end": 409.96,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "id": 181,
      "start": 409.96,
      "end": 410.76,
      "text": "I've never met anybody."
    },
    {
      "id": 182,
      "start": 410.76,
      "end": 412.44,
      "text": "It says, yeah, I'm like, my query runs slower."
    },
    {
      "id": 183,
      "start": 412.44,
      "end": 413.96,
      "text": "Yeah, yeah, great."
    },
    {
      "id": 184,
      "start": 413.96,
      "end": 417.92,
      "text": "Now, certainly there's a cost element, too, right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 185,
      "start": 417.92,
      "end": 419.84,
      "text": "You can pay millions of millions of dollars"
    },
    {
      "id": 186,
      "start": 419.84,
      "end": 422.24,
      "text": "to get that Microsoft, you know, some Microsoft"
    },
    {
      "id": 187,
      "start": 422.24,
      "end": 424.4,
      "text": "or some millisecond latency."
    },
    {
      "id": 188,
      "start": 424.4,
      "end": 425.4,
      "text": "Most people don't need that."
    },
    {
      "id": 189,
      "start": 425.4,
      "end": 426.52,
      "text": "We're the right tradeoff, it depends."
    },
    {
      "id": 190,
      "start": 426.8,
      "end": 433.8,
      "text": "But like, everybody would benefit from this, I think."
    },
    {
      "id": 191,
      "start": 437.64,
      "end": 438.96,
      "text": "OK."
    },
    {
      "id": 192,
      "start": 438.96,
      "end": 441.16,
      "text": "So in terms of the performance you can get"
    },
    {
      "id": 193,
      "start": 441.16,
      "end": 442.56,
      "text": "from these different queries, again,"
    },
    {
      "id": 194,
      "start": 442.56,
      "end": 444.84,
      "text": "so you have the three different phases, the bytecode version,"
    },
    {
      "id": 195,
      "start": 444.84,
      "end": 447.88,
      "text": "the unoptimized LLBM and the optimized LLBM."
    },
    {
      "id": 196,
      "start": 447.88,
      "end": 452.12,
      "text": "And again, you can see how this is log scale."
    },
    {
      "id": 197,
      "start": 452.12,
      "end": 457.12,
      "text": "But there's a pretty big jump between the bytecode version"
    },
    {
      "id": 198,
      "start": 457.12,
      "end": 461.44,
      "text": "and the simple LLBM pass one."
    },
    {
      "id": 199,
      "start": 461.44,
      "end": 463.92,
      "text": "And then depending on the complexity of the query,"
    },
    {
      "id": 200,
      "start": 463.92,
      "end": 468.2,
      "text": "the gap between the 0, 0, and 0, 2 between the diversion"
    },
    {
      "id": 201,
      "start": 468.2,
      "end": 470.36,
      "text": "will be slightly different."
    },
    {
      "id": 202,
      "start": 470.36,
      "end": 473.48,
      "text": "Again, scale factor one, all the queries"
    },
    {
      "id": 203,
      "start": 473.48,
      "end": 475.4,
      "text": "are running a single thread for the queries, right?"
    },
    {
      "id": 204,
      "start": 475.4,
      "end": 478.0,
      "text": "So you can use the other threads to compile"
    },
    {
      "id": 205,
      "start": 478.0,
      "end": 480.8,
      "text": "the compilation stuff."
    },
    {
      "id": 206,
      "start": 480.8,
      "end": 482.28,
      "text": "Again, but it's not just about performance,"
    },
    {
      "id": 207,
      "start": 482.28,
      "end": 487.36,
      "text": "it's also the debug ability and the maintenance of the system."
    },
    {
      "id": 208,
      "start": 487.36,
      "end": 492.16,
      "text": "So I want to do a quick run through a bunch"
    },
    {
      "id": 209,
      "start": 492.16,
      "end": 493.88,
      "text": "of different systems that are doing, again,"
    },
    {
      "id": 210,
      "start": 493.88,
      "end": 495.96,
      "text": "different variations of code compilation"
    },
    {
      "id": 211,
      "start": 495.96,
      "end": 499.64,
      "text": "of query generation or query compilation."
    },
    {
      "id": 212,
      "start": 499.64,
      "end": 502.04,
      "text": "And I sort of broke it up, losing to four categories."
    },
    {
      "id": 213,
      "start": 502.04,
      "end": 503.64,
      "text": "This is not scientific definitions."
    },
    {
      "id": 214,
      "start": 503.64,
      "end": 506.72,
      "text": "It's just how I think an easy way to categorize"
    },
    {
      "id": 215,
      "start": 506.72,
      "end": 507.96,
      "text": "and understand things."
    },
    {
      "id": 216,
      "start": 507.96,
      "end": 509.72,
      "text": "So the translation would be source-to-source stuff."
    },
    {
      "id": 217,
      "start": 509.72,
      "end": 511.32,
      "text": "We talked about beginning with IQ."
    },
    {
      "id": 218,
      "start": 511.32,
      "end": 513.72,
      "text": "The custom one will be, although actually hyper"
    },
    {
      "id": 219,
      "start": 513.72,
      "end": 515.44,
      "text": "should be over here, but on the other side."
    },
    {
      "id": 220,
      "start": 515.44,
      "end": 516.72,
      "text": "But these will be different systems"
    },
    {
      "id": 221,
      "start": 516.72,
      "end": 518.4,
      "text": "are doing different things."
    },
    {
      "id": 222,
      "start": 518.4,
      "end": 519.84,
      "text": "Sometimes they're using LLBM."
    },
    {
      "id": 223,
      "start": 519.84,
      "end": 522.6,
      "text": "Sometimes they're not."
    },
    {
      "id": 224,
      "start": 522.6,
      "end": 525.88,
      "text": "Or if it's CLR, if it's in Microsoft stuff,"
    },
    {
      "id": 225,
      "start": 525.88,
      "end": 527.4,
      "text": "then there's a bunch of Java databases"
    },
    {
      "id": 226,
      "start": 527.4,
      "end": 530.36,
      "text": "that are doing just the time published from a JDM."
    },
    {
      "id": 227,
      "start": 530.36,
      "end": 533.6,
      "text": "And then here's all the ones that are using the LLBM."
    },
    {
      "id": 228,
      "start": 533.6,
      "end": 536.56,
      "text": "And then the skull and bones are means these systems are dead."
    },
    {
      "id": 229,
      "start": 537.56,
      "end": 540.56,
      "text": "We've killed to CMU."
    },
    {
      "id": 230,
      "start": 540.56,
      "end": 543.4,
      "text": "Not proud of what had happened."
    },
    {
      "id": 231,
      "start": 543.4,
      "end": 547.56,
      "text": "So the very first system that did code specialization"
    },
    {
      "id": 232,
      "start": 547.56,
      "end": 549.28,
      "text": "was one of the first relational database systems."
    },
    {
      "id": 233,
      "start": 549.28,
      "end": 553.76,
      "text": "And as oftentimes in databases, IBM did it first."
    },
    {
      "id": 234,
      "start": 553.76,
      "end": 557.16,
      "text": "So the very first relational database, well,"
    },
    {
      "id": 235,
      "start": 557.16,
      "end": 559.44,
      "text": "the first major relational database system they were building,"
    },
    {
      "id": 236,
      "start": 559.44,
      "end": 562.56,
      "text": "there was a precursor to the system R out of the UK"
    },
    {
      "id": 237,
      "start": 562.56,
      "end": 565.76,
      "text": "called Peter Lee relational test vehicle."
    },
    {
      "id": 238,
      "start": 565.76,
      "end": 568.16,
      "text": "Which sounds like a prog rock band."
    },
    {
      "id": 239,
      "start": 568.16,
      "end": 569.16,
      "text": "But that was like a prototype."
    },
    {
      "id": 240,
      "start": 569.16,
      "end": 570.36,
      "text": "And the bunch of people that built that one"
    },
    {
      "id": 241,
      "start": 570.36,
      "end": 571.4,
      "text": "then went to go build a system R."
    },
    {
      "id": 242,
      "start": 571.4,
      "end": 574.0,
      "text": "The system R was the first real one."
    },
    {
      "id": 243,
      "start": 574.0,
      "end": 579.8,
      "text": "So back in the 70s, they had an early implementation"
    },
    {
      "id": 244,
      "start": 579.8,
      "end": 584.96,
      "text": "of code specialization or code generation for running queries."
    },
    {
      "id": 245,
      "start": 584.96,
      "end": 587.52,
      "text": "Again, think of like the 1970s, the harder it was terrible."
    },
    {
      "id": 246,
      "start": 587.52,
      "end": 590.12,
      "text": "The CPUs were slow, disk was slow, everything was terrible."
    },
    {
      "id": 247,
      "start": 590.12,
      "end": 592.88,
      "text": "So if you had it then interpret the query plan"
    },
    {
      "id": 248,
      "start": 592.88,
      "end": 595.08,
      "text": "on this really slow single threaded CPU,"
    },
    {
      "id": 249,
      "start": 595.08,
      "end": 597.48,
      "text": "that would just, it would take forever."
    },
    {
      "id": 250,
      "start": 597.48,
      "end": 600.04,
      "text": "So what they would do is they would have"
    }
  ],
  "language": "en"
}